The pre-trial material is public at least to the parties.
The analysis unit has found that the most professional criminals learn from the mistakes they make.
The smartest ones order the minutes of the district court, which can show, for example, that fingerprints have been found in the place.
The next time the thieves go hand in hand with gloves.
For the case, Deputy Chief of Police Tero Seppänen from the Häme Police, Tuomo Lepola from the Eastern Finnish Police, Sami Joutjärvi from the Joensuu Police Station, and Arto Tuomela from the Central Criminal Police.
The police collects and analyses information that is used to plan practical activities.
Against the background of a decrease in labour and financial numbers.
